=A0show fake demand, but it is just normal smart trading to=C2=A0hide your =
real demand. So in my schematic description above I said you could put in a=
 real order to buy 100 things and a spoof order to sell 1,000 things. But i=
n practice in many markets what you=E2=80=99d do is put in a=C2=A0hidden=C2=
=A0order to buy 100 things, so other traders wouldn=E2=80=99t see your dema=
nd, and a=C2=A0visible=C2=A0spoof order to sell 1,000 things, so they would=
. That is what NatWest did:More specifically, on hundreds of occasions, the=
