 this places a burden on the budget which could well end up getting monetiz=
ed and then generate even higher inflation and more withdrawals. In other w=
ords, Erdogan just made a very big bet on the power of (3,3).</p></blockquo=
te><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The =E2=80=9C(3, 3)=E2=80=9D meme is a sort=
 of casual adaptation of game-theory payoff notation. The idea is that if y=
ou sell your OHM that is bad for you (you don=E2=80=99t own OHM any more) a=
nd bad for everyone else who owns OHM (your selling pushes down the price o=
f OHM); if everyone sells,=C2=A0that has a payoff of=C2=A0=E2=80=9C(-3, -3)=
.=E2=80=9D But if you buy OHM and stake it, that is good for you (you get m=
ore OHM) and good for the other OHM holders=C2=A0(your buying pushes up the=
 price of OHM); if everyone stakes,=C2=A0that=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C(3, 3).=E2=
=80=9D The ordered pair represents payoffs for you and for the other player=
 in this game; the numbers are arbitrary.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A=
lso OHM pays a comically large interest rate (in OHM) to holders who stake =
their OHM. Currently it has an annual yield (again, in OHM) <a href=3D"http=
